author: COMSOL
description: This example illustrates the optimization of stacking sequence in a composite laminate based on the Hashin failure criterion. The composite laminate considered for the analysis has six layers with symmetric angle-ply layup. The carbon–epoxy material having transversely isotropic material properties is used as a lamina material. The optimization analysis is performed to find the optimum fiber orientation in each layer in order to make laminate safe and suitable under given loading conditions.
